Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Trim top of @eggplant{1}, then dice rest into ½-inch cubes. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with 1 TBSP @olive oil{1%tbsp} and the @fall spice blend{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until golden brown and softened, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Bring 1¼ cups salted water to a boil in a #medium pot{}. Once boiling, add @tri-colored quinoa{½%cup}. Reduce to a simmer, cover, and cook until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}. Place @dried cranberries{1%ounce} in a #small bowl{} with enough hot water to cover them. Combine minced shallots and @sherry vinegar{2%tbsp} in small bowl to marinate.

Whisk together 2 TBSP @olive oil{2%tbsp} and @honey{1%jar}. Season with salt and pepper. Pour in 1 TBSP sherry vinegar from marinating shallots and as much of the shallots as you like (we recommend 2 tsp).

Core and dice @Honeycrisp apple{1} into ½-inch cubes. Fluff cooked quinoa with a #fork{}. Drain any excess liquid.

Toss quinoa in a #large bowl{} with roasted eggplant, apple cubes, and @mixed greens{2%ounce}. Add in additional marinated shallots (to taste). Drain cranberries and toss into salad. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Divide between plates, and top with @walnuts{2%ounce}.

> This salad has autumn written all over it thanks to the combination of Honeycrisp apples, crunchy walnuts, and tart cranberries. Protein-packed quinoa adds some bulk, and a sweet sherry honey vinaigrette brings it all together.